Starting on this day 117 years ago, Jesse Livermore made his biggest profit to date shorting the market after the San Francisco Earthquake.  He lost all those profits betting against an uptrend he didn't believe in.  He stepped away and came back when conditions were right, and cleaned up. Timing is everything.  Know your market conditions.  There very well may be a big downturn in the very near future, but you'll have time to catch it when it happens. Remember "Don't fight the tape" overrules "don't fight the Fed".  $SPX $SPY $STUDY

Just a little history: back in 1979, the yield curve troughed after being negative for several months.  It never turned positive throughout the year and a recession didn't start until the beginning of 1980.  The whole time, core CPI went from a 7 handle to a 12 handle and the Fed Funds Rate went from a 10 to a 13.  The S&P 500 $SPX $SPY was up more than 7% during this period.  In 2023, it now appears the curve troughed a couple of weeks ago.
